16/08/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- State Department spokesman Sean McCormack announced on Tuesday (15 August) that the US and Montenegro have officially established diplomatic ties. 
The procedure was completed after the exchange of formal letters between US President George W. 
Bush and Montenegrin counterpart Filip Vujanovic. 
McCormack expressed Washington's desire for continued co-operation with Podgorica and praised the level of collaboration demonstrated by Montenegro and Serbia since the break-up of their former union. 
(Vijesti, DPA - 16/08/06; US State Department press release - 15/08/06)
